	abstract = {Non-nucleoside inhibitors of HIV-1 reverse transcriptase are being pursued through synthesis and assaying for anti-viral activity. Following computational analyses, the focus has been on the motif Het--NH--Ph--U, where Het is an aromatic heterocycle and U is an unsaturated, hydrophobic group. Previous investigations with Het=2-thiazoyl and 2-pyrimidinyl are extended here to triazinyl derivatives. The result is several NNRTIs in the 2--20nM range with negligible cytotoxicity and auspicious predicted pharmacological properties.},
